The paper presents a computational framework for modeling reaching movements in the presence of obstacles, which is relevant to robotics and control. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a stochastic optimal control framework that involves probabilistic collision avoidance constraints and a cost function, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the variability associated with human motion, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
